lines.text: it waits for the day
i will let it out
to give it a reason
to give it its might
i fear who i am becoming
i feel that-i'm loosing this struggle within
i can no longer restrain it
my strenght it is fading, i have to give in
fear of the dark it's growing inside of me
that one day will come to life
to save my beloved there is no escape
because my faith is horror and doom
hold down your head now
just let me pass by
don't feed my fear
if you don't want it out
i fear who i am becoming
i feel that-i'm loosing all beauty within
i can no longer restrain it
my strenght it is fading, i have to give in
fear of the dark it's growing inside of me
that one day will come to life
to save my beloved there is no escape
because my faith is horror and doom
long ago it came to me
and ever since that day
infected with its rage, but it ends today
fear of the dark it's growing inside of me
that one day will come to life
to save my beloved there is no escape
because my faith is horror and doom
